sentences: Esmée Denters (born 28 September 1988) is a Dutch singer and YouTube celebrity.
Denters started promoting herself as a musician online in 2006, covering songs by artists including Justin Timberlake and Natasha Bedingfield.
In May 2009, she released her debut studio album, Outta Here, and toured the United States with Timberlake.
In 2017, Denters released her EP These Days, followed by the EP Past, Present, Future in 2020.

2011–2014: Dismissal from Tennman Records ===

They performed the song at the Dance4Life 2012 charity event in Ahoy, Rotterdam.
Denters was dropped from Tennman Records that year.
On 24 February 2014, Denters returned to the stage, performing new music at Showcase Live in London.
On 24 September 2014, Denters released her first independent single "If I Could I Would" on iTunes and Spotify.
